<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFF9FF91FF028E0DFEA8FDEF" blockId="2.[151,630,501,560]" box="[151,288,535,560]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
(
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FF0A8E0DFE9FFDEF" box="[159,279,535,560]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1–6" captionStart-1="FIGURES7–11" captionStart-2="FIGURES 12–14" captionStartId-0="3.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,264,1961,1984]" captionStartId-2="5.[151,264,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox-0="[175,1404,195,1944]" captionTargetBox-1="[169,1376,231,1919]" captionTargetBox-2="[215,1379,210,1895]" captionTargetId-0="figure@3.[170,1417,183,1964]" captionTargetId-1="figure@4.[150,1436,205,1937]" captionTargetId-2="figure@5.[150,1436,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionTargetPageId-2="5" captionText-0="FIGURES 1–6. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (1) and lateral vieW (2), holotype male, lateral vieW (3); head, paratype female (4) and holotype male, dorSal vieW (5); female, lateral vieW (6)." captionText-1="FIGURES7–11. Neapion(N.) marquesae sp. nov.:male pygidium, dorSal (7) and lateral vieW (8);Spiculum gaStrale (9);peniS dorSal vieW (10); tegmen, dorSal vieW (11)." captionText-2="FIGURES 12–14. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: ovipoSitor coxite and StyluS (12); Spermatheca (13) and Spiculum ventral (14)." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/1209788/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/1209790/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/1209792/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Figs. 1–14</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C329657BFFF9FF91FF028E45FB23FCD7" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFF9FF91FF028E45FB23FCD7" blockId="2.[151,1437,607,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFF9FF91FF028E45FE82FDA7" bold="true" box="[151,266,607,632]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This new species is distinguished from the other 
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFF9FF91FCAB8E7BFCD1FDA7" box="[830,857,609,632]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">N.</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C334D73FFF9FF91FCFD8E7BFC6EFDA7" authorityName="Alonso-Zarazaga" authorityYear="1990" box="[872,998,609,632]" class="Insecta" family="Brentidae" genus="Neotropion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFF9FF91FCFD8E7BFC6EFDA7" box="[872,998,609,632]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Neotropion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) species by the elytra with Vestiture of dense, thin, off-white to dark brown scales (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FD1B8E9EFD72FD43" box="[654,762,644,669]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[175,1404,195,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,183,1964]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (1) and lateral vieW (2), holotype male, lateral vieW (3); head, paratype female (4) and holotype male, dorSal vieW (5); female, lateral vieW (6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209788/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Figs. 1–3</figureCitation>
), denser and thicker in the lateral regions of the pronotum, mesanepisternum, mesepimeron and metanepisternum (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FC988EBDFCF3FD1F" box="[781,891,679,704]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[175,1404,195,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,183,1964]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (1) and lateral vieW (2), holotype male, lateral vieW (3); head, paratype female (4) and holotype male, dorSal vieW (5); female, lateral vieW (6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209788/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Figs. 2–3</figureCitation>
); with eight raised areas in each elytron, two in the interVal 2 (the largest submedian and the smaller in the posterior half), four in interVal 4 (three in the anterior half and one in the posterior half) and one in each posterior third of interVals 5 and 6 (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FBCC8EF5FB15FCD7" box="[1113,1181,751,776]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[175,1404,195,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,183,1964]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (1) and lateral vieW (2), holotype male, lateral vieW (3); head, paratype female (4) and holotype male, dorSal vieW (5); female, lateral vieW (6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209788/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C329657BFFF9FF95FF528F0EFD34FDE2" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="557" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFF9FF91FF528F0EFB39FC8F" blockId="2.[151,1437,607,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFF9FF91FF528F0EFD9FFCF2" bold="true" box="[199,535,788,813]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Description. Measurements:</emphasis>
male 
<typeStatus id="54888852FFF9FF91FDC98F0EFD36FCF2" box="[604,702,788,813]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">holotype</typeStatus>
(in mm): length 2.96; rostrum length 0.80; maximum width 0.36; pronotum length 0.88 and maximum width 0.96; elytra length 2.20 and maximum width 1.20.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFF9FF91FF528F46FBEAFCAA" blockId="2.[151,1437,607,2037]" box="[199,1122,860,885]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFF9FF91FF528F46FEDAFCAA" bold="true" box="[199,338,860,885]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Integument</emphasis>
dark brown, antennae ferrugineous, legs light brown, abdomen black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFF9FF91FF528F65FB2EFBDA" blockId="2.[151,1437,607,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFF9FF91FF528F65FEB8FC47" bold="true" box="[199,304,895,920]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Vestiture</emphasis>
in general conspicuous, scales dense, heterogeneous, off-white to dark brown; meta- and mesorostrum scales more sparsely distributed, absent on the prorostrum apex; head and pronotal disc scales sparse, on pronotum centripetal pattern; elytra basal half with tan to light brown scales and two oblique dark macules from interVal 1 to 2; Ventral region with off-white scales (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FD4A8FF6FCC3FBDB" box="[735,843,1004,1029]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[175,1404,195,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,183,1964]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (1) and lateral vieW (2), holotype male, lateral vieW (3); head, paratype female (4) and holotype male, dorSal vieW (5); female, lateral vieW (6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209788/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Figs. 2–3</figureCitation>
), uniform abdominal Ventrites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFF9FF91FF528815FDAAFB4A" blockId="2.[151,1437,607,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFF9FF91FF528815FEB9FBF7" bold="true" box="[199,305,1039,1064]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Rostrum</emphasis>
curVed, robust, in side View conVex dorsally and Ventrally at mesorostral leVel (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FB3A8815FB7BFBF7" box="[1199,1267,1039,1064]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[175,1404,195,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,183,1964]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (1) and lateral vieW (2), holotype male, lateral vieW (3); head, paratype female (4) and holotype male, dorSal vieW (5); female, lateral vieW (6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209788/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), apex more or less acutely subulate; in dorsal View about 2.2 times longer than maximum width; 0.90 times pronotum length along midline; mesorostrum matte, laterally dilated (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FD73884DFCA1FBAF" box="[742,809,1111,1136]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[175,1404,195,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,183,1964]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (1) and lateral vieW (2), holotype male, lateral vieW (3); head, paratype female (4) and holotype male, dorSal vieW (5); female, lateral vieW (6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209788/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
), about 1.9 times larger than apex of prorostrum; apical 4/5 polished and finely punctuated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFF9FF91FF528885FBD1FAB2" blockId="2.[151,1437,607,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFF9FF91FF528885FE8FFB67" bold="true" box="[199,263,1183,1208]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Head</emphasis>
with frons slightly depressed with scales smaller than those around the eyes; subocular keel well deVeloped, extending beyond the posterior margin of the eyes; area between subocular keels microreticulate and impunctate. Eyes oblong-oVal, conVex (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FDC188FDFD10FADF" box="[596,664,1255,1280]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[175,1404,195,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,183,1964]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (1) and lateral vieW (2), holotype male, lateral vieW (3); head, paratype female (4) and holotype male, dorSal vieW (5); female, lateral vieW (6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209788/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Antennae inserted at basal 0.25 of rostrum length; scape 0.55 times mesorostral width, 1,75 times as long as wide, as long as club, 0.7 times club width; pedicel as long as wide, as long as desmomeres 1+2, desmomere 1-5 as long as wide, desmomere 6 as long as wide, subconical; club oblong, compact, 2 times as long as wide, as long as the last 5.5 desmomeres, sutures marked.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFF9FF91FF52896DFDCDF96F" blockId="2.[151,1437,607,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFF9FF91FF52896DFEAEFA4F" bold="true" box="[199,294,1399,1424]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum conical in dorsal View, slightly constricted before apex, about 0.91 as long as wide, base 1.5 times apex width, bisinuate with moderate median rounded projection toward scutellum; outline in lateral View slightly depressed anteriorly; pronotal disc with surface irregular, slightly depressed longitudinally and on both sides of midline, with sub-basal foVea; punctures coVered by scales. Scutellum length about 1.4 times maximum width, grades posteriorly into slender, awl-shaped basal angles with apex curVing slightly upwards in lateral View. Elytral length 1.83 times width, gibbose in profile; humeri salient; interstriae conVex, with eight raised areas of different lengths and heights (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FE768A55FDAEF9B7" box="[483,550,1615,1640]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[175,1404,195,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,183,1964]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (1) and lateral vieW (2), holotype male, lateral vieW (3); head, paratype female (4) and holotype male, dorSal vieW (5); female, lateral vieW (6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209788/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), as described in the diagnosis; striae Visible along the length, strongly punctate apically. Mesocoxae separated by about 0.3 times the mesocoxal diameter. Metasternal rim absent. Median foVea near posterior margin of metasternum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFF9FF91FF528AA6FE01F89F" blockId="2.[151,1437,607,2037]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFF9FF91FF528AA6FECBF90A" bold="true" box="[199,323,1724,1749]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Abdominal Ventrites with midline length ratios: 
<date id="FF8D1030FFF9FF91FC038AA6FB90F90A" box="[918,1048,1724,1749]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="1940-06-25" valueMax="1940-08-25" valueMin="1940-06-25">40–25–6–8</date>
–17; Ventrite 5 apically truncate; pygidium of incomplete apionine type (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FDF48AC5FD4FF927" box="[609,711,1759,1784]" captionStart="FIGURES7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1961,1984]" captionTargetBox="[169,1376,231,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[150,1436,205,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES7–11. Neapion(N.) marquesae sp. nov.:male pygidium, dorSal (7) and lateral vieW (8);Spiculum gaStrale (9);peniS dorSal vieW (10); tegmen, dorSal vieW (11)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209790/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Fig. 7, 8</figureCitation>
), semicircular, 0.5 times longer than wide, with distinct, deep, transVerse preapical sulcus incomplete laterally, not reaching side margins of pygidium, profile distinctly interrupted by sulcus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFF9FF95FF528B56FAF1FF27" blockId="2.[151,1437,607,2037]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,151,896]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="557" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFF9FF91FF528B56FDA7F8BA" bold="true" box="[199,559,1868,1893]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Male terminalia and genitalia</emphasis>
. Ninth sternite (spiculum gastrale) Y-shaped, manubrium ca. 1.85 times arm length (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FF648B75FEB2F857" box="[241,314,1903,1928]" captionStart="FIGURES7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1961,1984]" captionTargetBox="[169,1376,231,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[150,1436,205,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES7–11. Neapion(N.) marquesae sp. nov.:male pygidium, dorSal (7) and lateral vieW (8);Spiculum gaStrale (9);peniS dorSal vieW (10); tegmen, dorSal vieW (11)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209790/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Penis (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FE318B75FE72F857" box="[420,506,1903,1928]" captionStart="FIGURES7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1961,1984]" captionTargetBox="[169,1376,231,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[150,1436,205,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES7–11. Neapion(N.) marquesae sp. nov.:male pygidium, dorSal (7) and lateral vieW (8);Spiculum gaStrale (9);peniS dorSal vieW (10); tegmen, dorSal vieW (11)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209790/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) depressed, curVed, pedon with apical plate straight in side View, rounded and slightly constricted apically in dorsal View; tectum slender and with clear margins; temones length about 0.47 times pedon length; internal sac with two long (520 µm) and parallel sclerites, transVersely joined, forming a ‘tuningfork’ shaped structure. Tegmen (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFF9FF91FD948BC6FDC7F82B" box="[513,591,2012,2037]" captionStart="FIGURES7–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1961,1984]" captionTargetBox="[169,1376,231,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[150,1436,205,1937]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES7–11. Neapion(N.) marquesae sp. nov.:male pygidium, dorSal (7) and lateral vieW (8);Spiculum gaStrale (9);peniS dorSal vieW (10); tegmen, dorSal vieW (11)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209790/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) with tegminal plate fused to free ring; parameroid lobes slightly notched in the membranous area, microsetose apically, sclerotized area of each side with 5 macrochaetae and sensilla in front of each fenestra; fenestrae width 1.3 times length, separated about 0.4 times fenestral width; linea arquata Visible; prostegium protruding medially in square shape. Manubrium as long as basal piece, with apex rounded.
</paragraph>
