<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFFDFF95FF528D1EFAF3FEBB" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFFDFF95FF528D1EFE96FEC2" bold="true" box="[199,286,260,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Female</emphasis>
. In general, with the same external characteristics of the male, slight Variations in relation to the length and width of the body; rostrum weakly thinner, more slender, with a less squamous and brighter metarostrum in the female. The dark macula on basal half of elytra is conspicuous, as an inVerted “V”, from interVal 1 to 2 (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFFDFF95FABD8D56FAE2FEBB" box="[1320,1386,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1970,1993]" captionTargetBox="[175,1404,195,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[170,1417,183,1964]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: paratype female, dorSal (1) and lateral vieW (2), holotype male, lateral vieW (3); head, paratype female (4) and holotype male, dorSal vieW (5); female, lateral vieW (6)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209788/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFFDFF95FF528D75FB39FE73" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFFDFF95FF528D75FEF7FE57" bold="true" box="[199,383,367,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Measurements:</emphasis>
female 
<typeStatus id="54888852FFFDFF95FE748D6AFDC4FE57" box="[481,588,368,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">paratypes</typeStatus>
(mean in mm): length 3.00; rostrum length 0.82; maximum width 0.36; pronotum length 0.80 and maximum width 1.00; elytra length 2.26 and maximum width 1.40.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFFDFF95FF528DADFD34FDE2" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFFDFF95FF528DADFE1BFE0F" bold="true" box="[199,403,439,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. OVipositor (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFFDFF95FDA28DADFD1CFE0F" box="[567,660,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[215,1379,210,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–14. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: ovipoSitor coxite and StyluS (12); Spermatheca (13) and Spiculum ventral (14)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209792/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
): Coxite length about 2.9 times width, with microchaetae. Styli subcylindrical, length about 1.2 times width, with 7 macrochaetae. Spermatheca (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFFDFF95FBBC8DC6FBF1FE2B" box="[1065,1145,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[215,1379,210,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–14. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: ovipoSitor coxite and StyluS (12); Spermatheca (13) and Spiculum ventral (14)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209792/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) C-shaped, no nodulus or ramus; cornu as broad as the corpus, with a small apical protuberance. Spiculum Ventrale (
<figureCitation id="13082A75FFFDFF95FB598DE5FAAAFDC7" box="[1228,1314,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[215,1379,210,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[150,1436,193,1929]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12–14. Neapion (N.) marquesae sp. nov.: ovipoSitor coxite and StyluS (12); Spermatheca (13) and Spiculum ventral (14)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1209792/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) elongate, straight, apical plate membranous and setiferous.
</paragraph>
