<subSubSection id="C329657BFFFDFF95FF528EE6FED1FCA0" pageId="6" pageNumber="557" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8C36F0FFFDFF95FF528EE6FED1FCA0" blockId="6.[151,1436,151,896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis id="B947EAE2FFFDFF95FF528EE6FECEFCCA" bold="true" box="[199,326,764,789]" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Etymology</emphasis>
. This species is named in honor of Dr. Marinêz Isaac Marques, UniVersidade Federal de 
<collectingRegion id="49F7F812FFFDFF95FAF48EE7FF61FCE7" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, who encouraged the first author in his studies of weeVils, and who, for more than 20 years, contributed to ecological studies of the Curculionoidea in the Pantanal of 
<collectingRegion id="49F7F812FFFDFF95FCAD8F5FFC46FC83" box="[824,974,836,860]" country="Brazil" name="Mato Grosso" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Mato Grosso</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3247660FFFDFF95FC4E8F5EFBABFC82" box="[987,1059,836,861]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="557">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The specific epithet is a noun in the genitiVe case.
</paragraph>
